          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <placeName>371 Walnut St</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">near <placeName>13th St</placeName></p>
                              <p>For</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">The <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <placeName>
                                                  <hi rend="underline">America</hi>
                                        </placeName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>
                                        <add>לאיש אשר אלה לו התורה והחכמה הדעת והתבונה ידידי וידיד
                                                  נפשי</add>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>London</placeName>
                                        <date>29th Tebet 5611</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>Revd and dear Sir,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">I have <sic>considerd</sic> it a religious
                                        duty<lb/> on my part to address this day a Pastoral letter
                                        to the<lb/> much respect <persName>A. Hart Esq.</persName>
                                        President of your Congregation<lb/> to endeavour a
                                        reconciliation for indeed I must confess<lb/> fearless of
                                        any one that you Sir as a <add>כי ביצחק יקרא החכם השלם יצחק
                                                  בן אורי ז"ן בן אליעזר</add><lb/> cannot in any way
                                        be removed unless proper evidence<lb/> of any <add>יזנ"ה אתו
                                                  את הברכה מהברכה העליונה יהי שלום בחילו אין שטן
                                                  ואין</add> be regularly taken by Orthodox and<lb/>
                                        authenticated Jewish Ecclesiastics, thus I says if they<lb/>
                                        really wish to be reputed as Jews which I doubt<lb/> not but
                                        they are I have written to say that I am in<lb/> full hopes
                                        that shortly every member at
                                                  <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/> will
                                        loudly cry <add>פגע רע רק השקט ובטחה על אויביו יתגבר ולא
                                                  תעשינה ידיהם תושיה</add> I regret that<lb/> the
                                        days are very short (<date>Friday's</date>) and my
                                        occupations<lb/> are numerous otherwise I should send you a
                                        copy<lb/> I trust they will do all that is right. I have
                                        read<lb/> the whole of your letter attentively—now my
                                        Dr.<lb/> friend let me urge upon you and request it as
                                        a<lb/> particular favor as a brother or a child pray
                                        give<lb/> in (consistently) in whatever you can <add>מבקשי
                                                  רעתו</add><lb/> pray <sic>dont</sic> be hasty till
                                        all over <add>שליח צבור מוחזק מכמה שנים</add>
                                        <sic>dont</sic> allow your<lb/> enemies to laugh, enter, be
                                                  reinstated—<add>פסול חלילה</add> I doubt<lb/> not
                                        you will do it and will fully understand my meaning and<lb/>
                                        feelings—write to me <sic>dont</sic> spare me point out to
                                        me I am ready<lb/> and willing to serve you as I see you are
                                        in the right</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>I hope <persName>Mr. Hart</persName> will be generous to show
                                        you<lb/> my letter and communicate it at once to the<lb/>
                                        authorities and do all in your favor<add>?</add><lb/> as for
                                        your advice to the gang man here<lb/> to hesitate &amp;c I
                                        said nothing to him for<lb/> heaven knows he might take it
                                        as if I had<lb/> some particular views in it therefore
                                        silence on my part was the best—he is rather sly &amp;<lb/>
                                        I cannot find out what nature of a letter<lb/> he wrote
                                        (though he is <hi rend="underline">very friendly with
                                                  me</hi>)<lb/> to your congregation, what are his
                                        pretensions? in a<lb/> place they had you your Sermons, your literature<lb/>
                                        <del>a toll</del> an entire <sic><hi rend="underline"
                                                  >beginer</hi></sic> in every thing <del>he is
                                                  past</del><lb/> it is only 4 years he is here
                                                  <del>?</del><lb/> I thought therefore prudently
                                        not<lb/> to say a word to him, <del>though</del> I
                                                  <sic>learnt</sic> that he<lb/> wishes to be
                                        insured of the situation before he goes,<lb/> indeed—on what
                                        ground? I shall be most happy to<lb/> hear from you and hope
                                        the result will be good—<lb/> and favourable on your side;
                                        let me know something<lb/> of the above going man's
                                        application from here<lb/> let all this be in confidence.
                                        wishing you every<lb/> success and prosperity—I remain</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">Revd Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">yours very truly</p>
                              <p rend="indent(10)">
                                        <persName role="author">David Meldola</persName>
                              </p>
                              <p>The <persName>Revd. Dr. Schiller</persName> has been<lb/>
                                        <sic>choosen</sic> as minister (not <add>ואת בריתי (ברית
                                                  שלום) אקים את יצח"ק</add>) of
                                                  <placeName>Manchester</placeName><lb/> this is a
                                                  <sic>begining</sic> a Cardinal only, at present,
                                                  <hi rend="underline">he</hi><lb/> indeed is the
                                        ally the <hi rend="underline">man</hi>—<add>חכי כמעא עד
                                                  יעבור זעם</add><lb/> not the mere puff and
                                        humbugary of initials <persName>Dr
                                        Ph<add>?</add></persName></p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Please let me know candidly the effect of my letter<lb/>
                                        <add>כי הדור פרוץ והשעה צריכה לכך ודי למבין</add></p>
                              <pb n="4"/>
                              <p>Let me request of you that any thing I might<lb/> have said to be
                                        in the <hi rend="underline">greatest confidence</hi><lb/> as
                                        the young man is quite on friendly terms<lb/> with me and
                                        should not wish him to think<lb/> that I have even mentioned
                                        his name<lb/>
                                        <persName>Rabbi Nissim</persName> is at present at
                                                  <placeName>Paris</placeName><lb/> on his
                                                  journey—<persName>Mr D Pizinbert</persName> respects<lb/>
                                        <hi rend="underline">pray secrecy:</hi></p>
                    </body>
